== Boxer Name ==
The USS Boxer CV-21 was named, as most WWII era carriers were, for a battle in which US forces were engaged. In this case, the Boxer Rebellion in China. It was not named for any HMS Boxer. Nor, to my knowledge, has any other US warship been named to a British warship. [[User:Wilsonse|Wilsonse]] ([[User talk:Wilsonse|talk]]) 03:27, 28 September 2014 (UTC)<ref>http://www.history.navy.mil/faqs/faq63-1.htm</ref><ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_ship_naming_conventions</ref>
